<p>we are generating xsd-files from annotated Java classes. In this classes we also use the @XmlJavaTypeAdapter annotation to map a String to our Java classes. Is it possible to let schemagen create simple types for those classes, so that people who want to create Java classes out of this xsd create the correct classes?</p>  <p>Bindings.xjb</p>  <pre><code>&lt;xjc:javaType xmlType="dlz:XYId" name="de.xy.db.XYId"             adapter="de.xy.xmladapter.StringXYIdXmlAdapter" /&gt;   </code></pre>  <p>abc.xsd</p>  <pre><code>&lt;simpleType name="XYId"&gt;     &lt;restriction base="string" /&gt; &lt;/simpleType&gt; </code></pre>  <p>With these two files JAXB can create the correct Java classes.</p>